    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Exterior shutters, usually louvered shutters or jalousies, characterized by being hinged at the top and opening from the window like an awning instead of horizontally. They are designed to provide protection from severe storms.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
